1
00:00:02,202 --> 00:00:04,236
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON</i> THE PRETENDER.    
                YES, MR. PARKER.


2
00:00:04,305 --> 00:00:08,607
    <i> ANGELO IS SEARCHING</i>        
    <i> THE INTERNET</i>               
    <i> FOR ANY SIGNS OF JAROD NOW.</i>


3
00:00:08,675 --> 00:00:12,577
SL-27.                          
WHAT DOES IT MEAN, JACOB?       


4
00:00:14,248 --> 00:00:17,215
    <i> [ Miss Parker ]</i>            
    <i> SL 27. WHAT DOES IT MEAN?</i>  


5
00:00:25,693 --> 00:00:27,625
[ Tires Screeching ]            


6
00:00:42,709 --> 00:00:47,045
    DOES HE HAVE A NAME?        
    THEY'RE CALLING HIM JAROD.  


7
00:00:47,113 --> 00:00:51,049
        HE MISSES HIS PARENTS.  
HE'LL FORGET THEM SOON ENOUGH.  


8
00:00:53,854 --> 00:00:58,089
    ♪ KRI KRA TOAD'S FOOT ♪     


9
00:00:58,158 --> 00:01:03,561
        ♪ GEESE WALK BAREFOOT ♪ 


10
00:01:14,708 --> 00:01:17,976
    - FOUND THESE BLUEPRINTS    
      IN THE GUTTER.            
    - HE'S NEARBY. FIND HIM!    


11
00:01:18,045 --> 00:01:19,945
LET'S MOVE! GO!                 


12
00:01:46,474 --> 00:01:50,275
<i>[ Car Door Opens, Closes ]</i>      
<i>[ Footsteps ]</i>                   


13
00:01:52,679 --> 00:01:54,646
            <i> [ Bottle Rattling ]</i>


14
00:01:59,419 --> 00:02:01,352
<i>[ Clanking ]</i>                    


15
00:02:01,421 --> 00:02:04,055
<i>[ Footsteps Departing ]</i>         


16
00:02:20,206 --> 00:02:22,508
            HEY!                


17
00:02:23,844 --> 00:02:26,144
BLUE SEDAN.                     
            GET IN!             


18
00:02:28,849 --> 00:02:31,550
        THIS IS PARKER.         
        WE'RE IN PURSUIT        
        OF A BLUE SEDAN.        


19
00:02:34,722 --> 00:02:37,155
<i>[ Thumping ]</i>                    


20
00:02:52,039 --> 00:02:54,706
<i>[ Crying ]</i>                      


21
00:02:56,210 --> 00:02:59,711
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>               


22
00:03:47,260 --> 00:03:49,361
        [ Knocking ]            
        CHRISTINE!              


23
00:03:49,430 --> 00:03:51,095
<i>CHRISTINE?</i>                      


24
00:03:59,373 --> 00:04:01,839
        JAROD?                  
                    I'M SORRY,  
                    CHRISTINE.  


25
00:04:01,908 --> 00:04:04,876
            I KNOW IT'S LATE.   
    IT'S 3:00 IN THE MORNING.   
    GOD ISN'T EVEN AWAKE.       


26
00:04:04,945 --> 00:04:09,013
        I KNOW. LISTEN,         
        I NEED TO MOVE BACK IN  
        FOR A LITTLE WHILE.     


27
00:04:09,082 --> 00:04:11,215
    NOT SMELLIN' LIKE THAT      
    YOU'RE NOT.                 


28
00:04:11,284 --> 00:04:13,518
            PLEASE.             
LOOK, JAROD,                    


29
00:04:13,587 --> 00:04:17,355
I OWE YOU BIG TIME FOR          
WHAT YOU DID FOR ME, BUT MY     
HUSBAND'S COMIN' BACK TOMORROW. 


30
00:04:17,424 --> 00:04:20,559
IF AXE FINDS A MAN LIVIN'       
UPSTAIRS, HE'LL HAVE A STROKE.  
                <i> [ Soft Cry ]</i>   


31
00:04:22,062 --> 00:04:24,062
        <i> OH, MY GOD.</i>            


32
00:04:26,266 --> 00:04:28,267
WHERE DID YOU GET IT?           


33
00:04:29,903 --> 00:04:32,070
A MAN THREW HIM IN THE DUMPSTER.


34
00:04:32,139 --> 00:04:34,239
                    <i> OH, MY GOD.</i>


35
00:04:34,308 --> 00:04:36,541
HOW COULD SOMEONE DO THAT?      


36
00:04:36,610 --> 00:04:38,543
HOW COULD SOMEONE               
THROW AWAY A BABY?              


37
00:04:38,612 --> 00:04:42,147
    IT'S A CRAZY WORLD.         
    BABIES HAVIN' BABIES,       


38
00:04:42,215 --> 00:04:46,585
            PEOPLE DON'T KNOW   
            WHAT THEY WANT      
            OR WHAT THEY HAVE.  


39
00:04:46,653 --> 00:04:48,687
IT'S FREEZING IN HERE.          


40
00:04:49,956 --> 00:04:52,991
YOU HAVE TO CALL THE POLICE.    


41
00:04:54,427 --> 00:04:57,996
I'M THE ONLY FAMILY             
HE HAS RIGHT NOW.               


42
00:04:58,065 --> 00:05:02,067
HE'S COLD, HE'S SCARED,         
AND HE'S ALONE.                 


43
00:05:03,904 --> 00:05:05,937
DON'T YOU LIKE BABIES?          


44
00:05:08,141 --> 00:05:10,075
            OF COURSE.          


45
00:05:10,143 --> 00:05:12,944
IT'S JUST THAT IF AXE           
DIDN'T GET THE JOB IN HOUSTON,  


46
00:05:13,013 --> 00:05:15,213
        <i> HE'LL HAVE A STROKE</i>    
        <i> IF HE COMES BACK</i>       
        <i> AND FINDS A BABY HERE.</i> 


47
00:05:15,282 --> 00:05:17,615
    - HE DOESN'T LIKE BABIES?   
    - NO.                       


48
00:05:17,684 --> 00:05:19,717
        YES.                    
        THAT'S NOT THE POINT.   


49
00:05:22,790 --> 00:05:25,390
        - HE'S HUNGRY.          
        - HOW CAN YOU TELL?     


50
00:05:25,458 --> 00:05:27,292
BECAUSE I'M HUNGRY.             


51
00:05:28,862 --> 00:05:32,330
    WANNA-- WANNA LAY DOWN?     


52
00:05:32,399 --> 00:05:35,066
THERE YOU GO.                   
 THERE YOU GO.                  


53
00:05:45,545 --> 00:05:49,614
WHY-WHY WOULD JAROD RISK        
GETTING CAUGHT OVER             
A RANDOM SET OF BLUEPRINTS?     


54
00:05:49,683 --> 00:05:54,752
[ Chuckles ]                    
WHERE JAROD'S CONCERNED,        
THERE'S NEVER ANYTHING RANDOM.  


55
00:05:54,821 --> 00:05:56,754
        HMM.                    


56
00:05:56,823 --> 00:05:59,924
        BOY GENIUS IS           
        A REGULAR I.M. PEI.     


57
00:05:59,993 --> 00:06:02,159
    WAIT.                       


58
00:06:04,297 --> 00:06:06,464
WHAT'S THIS? SL 27?             


59
00:06:17,010 --> 00:06:19,010
                I'LL BE AROUND. 


60
00:06:22,549 --> 00:06:25,316
    ♪ KRI KRA TOAD'S FOOT ♪     


61
00:06:25,385 --> 00:06:28,153
        ♪ GEESE WALK BAREFOOT ♪ 


62
00:06:28,221 --> 00:06:30,856
    ♪ KRI KRA TOAD'S FOOT ♪     


63
00:06:30,924 --> 00:06:34,425
<i>♪ GEESE WALK BAREFOOT ♪</i>         


64
00:06:34,494 --> 00:06:37,061
    <i> WHO TAUGHT YOU THAT SONG?</i>  


65
00:06:38,365 --> 00:06:41,199
                I DON'T KNOW.   


66
00:06:41,267 --> 00:06:43,869
            MY MOTHER, I THINK. 


67
00:06:43,937 --> 00:06:46,571
            YOU THINK?          


68
00:06:46,640 --> 00:06:49,373
    WHEN I WAS LITTLE,          
    I WAS TAKEN FROM MY FAMILY. 


69
00:06:49,442 --> 00:06:52,143
            <i> I WAS RAISED</i>       
            <i> BY SOME PEOPLE--</i>   


70
00:06:52,212 --> 00:06:55,513
PEOPLE THAT HAD NO BUSINESS     
DEALING WITH CHILDREN.          


71
00:06:56,816 --> 00:06:59,884
    I'M SORRY.                  


72
00:06:59,953 --> 00:07:02,954
LOOK, JAROD, I APPRECIATE       
EVERYTHING YOU DID FOR ME.      


73
00:07:03,023 --> 00:07:06,157
<i>THAT PHONY LAWSUIT</i>              
<i>THAT LADY FILED AGAINST</i>         
<i>THE SHOP WOULD HAVE BUSTED ME...</i>


74
00:07:06,226 --> 00:07:09,627
IF YOU HADN'T STEPPED IN,       
BUT, STILL, I CAN'T LET YOU--   
        <i> [ Jarod, Babytalk ]</i>    


75
00:07:13,166 --> 00:07:15,100
            <i> [ Baby Cries Out ]</i> 


76
00:07:16,636 --> 00:07:20,638
    HOLLER DOWNSTAIRS           
    IF YOU NEED ANY HELP, OKAY? 
CHRISTINE?                      


77
00:07:22,275 --> 00:07:24,743
            THANKS.             


78
00:07:29,382 --> 00:07:33,351
[ Man ] DOES HE HAVE A NAME?    
    [ Man #2 ]                  
    THEY'RE CALLING HIM JAROD.  


79
00:07:33,420 --> 00:07:37,288
        HE MISSES HIS PARENTS.  
HE'LL FORGET THEM               
SOON ENOUGH.                    


80
00:08:04,084 --> 00:08:06,417
    [ Tones Beeping ]           


81
00:08:08,288 --> 00:08:12,123
                    [ Ringing ] 
THIS IS SYDNEY.                 


82
00:08:12,191 --> 00:08:15,727
HOW COULD SOMEBODY              
ABANDON A CHILD?                
JAROD.                          


83
00:08:15,795 --> 00:08:17,962
        I MEAN, SOMETHING       
        SO VULNERABLE,          


84
00:08:18,031 --> 00:08:20,298
    SO DEFENSELESS.             


85
00:08:20,367 --> 00:08:25,470
        HOW COULD THEY DO THAT? 
IS THIS ABOUT YOUR PARENTS?     


86
00:08:25,539 --> 00:08:28,406
        IT'S ABOUT ALL PARENTS. 
        [ Sydney Sighs ]        


87
00:08:28,474 --> 00:08:31,276
WELL, THERE'S                   
NO EASY ANSWER TO THAT.         


88
00:08:31,345 --> 00:08:34,712
WHO KNOWS WHAT, UH--            
WHAT PRESSURES SOME PEOPLE FACE.


89
00:08:34,781 --> 00:08:39,049
IS THIS WHAT YOU WERE           
LOOKING FOR EARLIER             
AT THAT ARCHITECTURAL FIRM?     


90
00:08:39,118 --> 00:08:43,555
THOSE BLUEPRINTS?               
IS THAT A LEAD TO YOUR PARENTS? 


91
00:08:43,623 --> 00:08:46,024
        YOU'LL FIGURE IT OUT.   


92
00:08:48,261 --> 00:08:50,261
                        HEY.    


93
00:09:06,647 --> 00:09:11,215
[ Clears Throat ]               
IT'S, UH,                       
FOR MY LITTLE GIRL.             


94
00:09:11,284 --> 00:09:15,020
    SHE'S VERY FORTUNATE TO HAVE
    SUCH AN ATTENTIVE FATHER.   


95
00:09:18,025 --> 00:09:20,391
I, UH, DID                      
THE SEARCH YOU REQUESTED.       


96
00:09:20,460 --> 00:09:24,128
FOUND TWO INACTIVE              
LICENSE PLATES WITH "SL 27,"    


97
00:09:24,197 --> 00:09:27,365
BUT BOTH OWNERS                 
DIED IN THE '70s.               


98
00:09:27,434 --> 00:09:29,834
SL 27 IS ALSO THE GENERIC NAME  
FOR AN ANTIBIOTIC...            


99
00:09:29,903 --> 00:09:33,538
DEVELOPED BY AN ISRAELI         
PHARMACEUTICAL COMPANY          
IN 1983.                        


100
00:09:33,607 --> 00:09:36,207
    THAT'S BEYOND               
    THE DATE OF SIGNIFICANCE.   


101
00:09:36,276 --> 00:09:38,977
    WELL,                       


102
00:09:39,046 --> 00:09:42,246
IF YOU TOLD ME MORE, SYDNEY,    
I MIGHT BE ABLE TO HELP.        


103
00:09:42,315 --> 00:09:45,116
    BROOTS, IT'S BEST THAT...   


104
00:09:45,185 --> 00:09:48,086
            NOBODY ELSE         
            BE INVOLVED IN THIS.


105
00:09:48,154 --> 00:09:52,824
        <i> BROOTS,</i>                
        <i> ANYTHING ON SL 27 YET?</i> 


106
00:09:52,893 --> 00:09:55,626
UH--                            


107
00:09:55,695 --> 00:09:59,530
PERHAPS YOU BOTH                
SHOULD HAVE A TALK.             


108
00:10:01,968 --> 00:10:04,402
<i>[ Keyboard Clacking ]</i>           


109
00:10:12,045 --> 00:10:15,212
        <i> [ Knocking ]</i>           


110
00:10:15,281 --> 00:10:17,816
            SHH.                
                <i> STILL SLEEPIN'?</i>


111
00:10:17,884 --> 00:10:19,884
<i>LIKE A BABY.</i>                    


112
00:10:24,991 --> 00:10:27,224
        - WHAT ARE YOU DOIN'?   
        - SETTING IT UP.        


113
00:10:27,294 --> 00:10:31,062
IF ANYBODY FILES A MISSING      
PERSONS REPORT WITH THE POLICE  
DEPARTMENT, I'LL GET A SIGNAL.  


114
00:10:31,131 --> 00:10:34,165
    JAROD, YOU CAN'T            
    KEEP THIS CHILD.            


115
00:10:34,233 --> 00:10:36,667
    <i> LAST NIGHT IS ONE THING,</i>   
    <i> BUT SOMEWHERE,</i>             


116
00:10:36,736 --> 00:10:39,270
        SOMEBODY'S LOOKING      
        FOR THIS BABY.          


117
00:10:39,338 --> 00:10:42,740
I'VE BEEN MONITORING EVERY      
POLICE CHANNEL, EVERY TELEVISION
STATION, EVERY NEWSPAPER.       


118
00:10:42,809 --> 00:10:45,043
<i>NOBODY'S LOOKING FOR HIM.</i>       
        BUT, JAROD--            


119
00:10:45,112 --> 00:10:47,112
    SOMEBODY THREW HIM          
    IN A DUMPSTER.              


120
00:10:47,180 --> 00:10:49,280
DO YOU WANT ME TO TURN HIM OVER 
TO THAT PERSON?                 


121
00:10:51,851 --> 00:10:55,553
    IF HIS MOTHER'S             
    OUT THERE SEARCHING,        
    I'LL FIND HER.              


122
00:10:55,622 --> 00:10:57,956
<i>BUT I'M NOT GONNA</i>               
<i>GIVE HIM TO ANYBODY...</i>          


123
00:10:58,024 --> 00:11:02,360
<i>TILL I KNOW</i>                     
<i>HE'S GONNA BE OKAY.</i>             


124
00:11:02,429 --> 00:11:04,395
    I DON'T WANT HIM            
    TO GROW UP ALONE.           


125
00:11:05,932 --> 00:11:08,766
    -<i> [ Baby Crying ]</i>           
    - ARE YOU HUNGRY AGAIN?     


126
00:11:08,835 --> 00:11:12,303
    - THAT'S NOT A BOTTLE CRY.  
    - HOW DO YOU KNOW?          


127
00:11:12,372 --> 00:11:14,538
        SEVEN YOUNGER           
        BROTHERS AND SISTERS.   


128
00:11:14,607 --> 00:11:16,540
            BETTER CHANGE HIM.  


129
00:11:21,081 --> 00:11:23,747
        <i> [ Crying Continues ]</i>   


130
00:11:25,618 --> 00:11:28,619
I KILLED THE SECURITY CAMERAS,  
AND I SWEPT THE ROOM FOR BUGS.  


131
00:11:28,688 --> 00:11:32,223
            I THINK WE'RE SAFE. 
YOU THINK?                      


132
00:11:32,292 --> 00:11:34,359
        ONE NEVER KNOWS         
        IN THE CENTRE, DO ONE?  


133
00:11:34,427 --> 00:11:36,427
        LET'S PROCEED.          


134
00:11:38,531 --> 00:11:41,599
THIS BELONGED TO                
ONE OF THE CHILDREN MY MOTHER   
RESCUED FROM THE CENTRE.        


135
00:11:41,667 --> 00:11:43,601
        LOOK AT THIS.           


136
00:11:45,305 --> 00:11:48,038
            "SL 27."            


137
00:11:48,107 --> 00:11:50,308
        WHY DID YOU KEEP        
        THIS INFORMATION SECRET?


138
00:11:51,778 --> 00:11:54,579
WHY, I COULD ASK                
THE SAME QUESTION OF YOU.       


139
00:12:00,086 --> 00:12:05,189
        WHEN MY BROTHER         
        REGAINED CONSCIOUSNESS, 
        HE WROTE THIS TO ME.    


140
00:12:08,895 --> 00:12:10,828
            HMM.                


141
00:12:10,897 --> 00:12:16,000
        THERE HAS TO BE A CLUE  
        IN THE CALCULATIONS     
        THAT JAROD DROPPED.     


142
00:12:16,069 --> 00:12:19,938
    BROOTS, KEEP ON SEARCHING   
    FOR THAT CONNECTION.        


143
00:12:23,075 --> 00:12:25,710
LOOK, I DON'T KNOW IF           
YOU GUYS MISSED IT, BUT, UH,    


144
00:12:25,778 --> 00:12:30,849
THE ONLY PEOPLE WHO KNOW        
ABOUT THIS SL 27 THING          
ARE EITHER DEAD OR COMATOSE.    


145
00:12:32,385 --> 00:12:35,453
        AND THOSE PEOPLE        
        ARE IMPORTANT TO US...  


146
00:12:35,521 --> 00:12:38,655
            LIKE YOUR DAUGHTER  
            IS TO YOU.          


147
00:12:38,724 --> 00:12:43,228
    I'M ASKING FOR YOUR HELP,   
    BROOTS,                     


148
00:12:43,296 --> 00:12:45,229
                AS A FRIEND.    


149
00:12:48,635 --> 00:12:50,868
        PLEASE.                 


150
00:12:57,377 --> 00:12:59,477
<i>[ Buzzing ]</i>                     


151
00:13:09,522 --> 00:13:12,023
            WHAT IS HE DOING?   


152
00:13:12,091 --> 00:13:17,728
HE APPEARS TO BE                
EXPRESSING HIS INDIVIDUALISM.   
                IS THAT GOOD?   


153
00:13:17,797 --> 00:13:21,499
<i>[ Raines ]</i>                      
<i>IT'S DANGEROUS.</i>                 


154
00:13:21,568 --> 00:13:25,069
ANGELO, I WANT YOU              
TO RUN A CHECK...               


155
00:13:25,137 --> 00:13:29,306
    ON EVERY ASPECT             
    OF CENTRE SECURITY.         


156
00:13:29,375 --> 00:13:34,945
EVERY SYSTEM, EVERY LEVEL,      
EVERY MODE OF                   
ACCESS AND EGRESS.              


157
00:13:35,014 --> 00:13:39,384
OPTICAL, PHYSICAL, ELECTRONIC-- 
[ Wheezing ]                    


158
00:13:39,452 --> 00:13:41,752
    EVERYTHING.                 


159
00:13:41,821 --> 00:13:44,189
<i>DO YOU UNDERSTAND?</i>              


160
00:13:45,858 --> 00:13:48,125
        ANGELO?                 


161
00:14:11,785 --> 00:14:13,551
[ Buzzer Clicks Off ]           


162
00:14:36,209 --> 00:14:39,177
<i>[ Chatter, Baby Crying ]</i>        


163
00:14:39,245 --> 00:14:41,245
<i>EXCUSE ME, MA'AM.</i>               
        I'LL BE RIGHT WITH YOU. 


164
00:14:45,585 --> 00:14:50,321
<i>YES, I'M LOOKING AT THE FILE.</i>   
<i>WE'VE PLACED A CALL TO</i>          
<i>THE BIOLOGICAL GRANDPARENTS,</i>    


165
00:14:50,389 --> 00:14:55,193
    BUT THE STATUS              
    IS STILL UNCLEAR.           


166
00:14:55,261 --> 00:14:58,929
- SURE. CAN I HELP YOU?         
- WE'D LIKE TO TALK TO SOMEBODY 
  ABOUT A MISSIN' CHILD.        


167
00:14:58,998 --> 00:15:02,132
I'LL BE ONE MORE MINUTE.        
NO, IT'S AGAINST THE LAW...     


168
00:15:02,201 --> 00:15:06,871
<i>TO PREMATURELY PLACE A CHILD</i>    
<i>WITHOUT THE SIGNATURE OF</i>        
<i>A BIOLOGICAL FAMILY MEMBER.</i>     


169
00:15:06,940 --> 00:15:10,375
I REALIZE YOU LOVE THE BABY,    
BUT THIS IS THE WAY             
IT HAS TO BE HANDLED.           


170
00:15:46,546 --> 00:15:51,048
    I KNOW THIS IS HARD, JAROD, 
    BUT I THINK                 
    IT'S THE BEST THING--       


171
00:15:51,117 --> 00:15:53,050
JAROD?                          


172
00:15:53,119 --> 00:15:56,754
        ARE YOU INSANE?         
        YOU CAN'T JUST WALK OUT 
        WITH THIS BABY.         


173
00:15:56,823 --> 00:16:00,692
WELL, I CAN'T                   
LEAVE HIM WITH THEM.            
JAROD, HE DOESN'T BELONG TO YOU.


174
00:16:00,760 --> 00:16:04,362
            [ Sighs ]           
            I KNOW.             


175
00:16:04,430 --> 00:16:06,364
HE BELONGS WITH HIS PARENTS,    


176
00:16:06,433 --> 00:16:09,667
OR WITH SOMEONE WHO LOVES HIM.  


177
00:16:12,105 --> 00:16:16,407
TWENTY-FOUR HOURS.              
THEN WE TAKE THE BABY           
TO THE POLICE NO MATTER WHAT.   


178
00:16:16,475 --> 00:16:18,476
                        DEAL?   


179
00:16:21,614 --> 00:16:23,848
DEAL.                           


180
00:16:23,917 --> 00:16:26,851
    ONE MORE THING.             
    GIVE HIM A NAME, WILL YA?   


181
00:16:26,920 --> 00:16:30,054
HE HAS A NAME.                  


182
00:16:30,123 --> 00:16:32,490
I JUST HAVE TO                  
FIND OUT WHAT IT IS.            


183
00:16:44,804 --> 00:16:48,038
WHAT IS IT?                     
    THEY ALL HAVE RED DECALS.   


184
00:16:49,842 --> 00:16:54,745
    THE MAN WHO DUMPED THIS BABY
    HAD THE EXACT SAME DECAL    
    ON THE BACK OF HIS CAR.     


185
00:16:58,218 --> 00:17:00,384
<i>WHAT ARE YOU SAYIN'?</i>            


186
00:17:02,021 --> 00:17:04,355
    A COP THREW THIS BABY AWAY. 


187
00:17:16,870 --> 00:17:19,704
            TALK TO ME, BROOTS. 
    YOU'LL NEVER GUESS          
    WHAT I FOUND OUT.           


188
00:17:19,773 --> 00:17:22,073
THE ARCHITECTURAL FIRM          
YOU CHASED JAROD FROM WAS--     


189
00:17:22,141 --> 00:17:24,842
        THE SAME ONE            
        THAT BUILT THE CENTRE.  


190
00:17:24,911 --> 00:17:28,245
HOW DID YOU KNOW THAT?          
                    [ Ringing ] 


191
00:17:28,314 --> 00:17:30,514
THIS IS SYDNEY.                 
                [ Jarod ]       
                ANY LUCK?       


192
00:17:30,583 --> 00:17:33,918
                WITH WHAT?      
<i>WELL, HELLO, MISS PARKER.</i>       


193
00:17:33,986 --> 00:17:36,354
                SL 27.          


194
00:17:36,422 --> 00:17:39,490
    THOSE CALCULATIONS, JAROD-- 
    WHAT DO THEY MEAN?          


195
00:17:39,559 --> 00:17:42,159
                JUST DIGGING UP 
                SOME MORE DIRT  
                ON THE CENTRE.  


196
00:17:42,228 --> 00:17:45,296
                I DON'T FOLLOW. 
        <i> DO THE MATH, SYDNEY.</i>   


197
00:17:45,365 --> 00:17:47,098
            IT DOESN'T ADD UP.  


198
00:17:47,167 --> 00:17:50,734
    <i> I'M SURPRISED THAT BROOTS</i>  
    <i> HASN'T FIGURED IT OUT YET.</i> 


199
00:17:51,604 --> 00:17:54,171
        - DIRT.                 
        -<i> I GOTTA GO.</i>           


200
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:56,641
    <i> IT'S THE BABY'S NAP TIME.</i>  


201
00:17:56,710 --> 00:17:58,475
            DID HE SAY BABY?    


202
00:18:00,146 --> 00:18:02,413
    <i> I'LL BE DAMNED.</i>            


203
00:18:02,482 --> 00:18:05,216
    6.32 MILLION                
    CUBIC FEET OF DIRT...       


204
00:18:05,285 --> 00:18:08,519
    WAS CARTED OFF              
    FOR THE CENTRE'S            
    UNDERGROUND CONSTRUCTION.   


205
00:18:08,588 --> 00:18:12,056
<i>BUT THE CENTRE'S</i>                
<i>26 SUBLEVELS ONLY OCCUPY...</i>     


206
00:18:12,125 --> 00:18:15,426
6.16 MILLION CUBIC FEET.        


207
00:18:17,530 --> 00:18:20,865
    THERE'S ENOUGH MISSING DIRT 
    FOR ANOTHER SUBLEVEL.       


208
00:18:21,968 --> 00:18:23,901
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>SL 27.</i>                          


209
00:18:25,272 --> 00:18:28,873
    SUBLEVEL 27.                


210
00:18:32,412 --> 00:18:34,812
        THIS IS MY MOTHER.      


211
00:18:34,881 --> 00:18:36,814
    WE'RE GOING TO FIND YOURS.  


212
00:18:36,883 --> 00:18:40,752
I PROMISE.                      
<i>[ Christine ]</i>                   
<i>WELL, THAT'S A SIGHT.</i>           


213
00:18:46,659 --> 00:18:48,993
        YOU AND AXE EVER THINK  
        ABOUT HAVING KIDS?      
                        <i> AXE?</i>   


214
00:18:49,062 --> 00:18:52,597
                NO. NO WAY.     


215
00:18:52,666 --> 00:18:55,600
        BESIDES, I GOT THE SHOP 
        TO WORRY ABOUT.         


216
00:18:55,669 --> 00:18:57,602
    ANY LUCK                    
    WITH THAT LICENSE PLATE?    


217
00:18:57,670 --> 00:19:00,772
    NOT YET.                    
    I HAVE TO GET INSIDE        
    THE POLICE DEPARTMENT...    


218
00:19:00,840 --> 00:19:04,542
AND FIND OUT                    
WHO WAS DRIVING THAT CAR,       
BUT I'M GOING TO NEED YOUR HELP.


219
00:19:04,610 --> 00:19:07,144
    JAROD, I'VE GOT CUSTOMERS.  
    I CAN'T GO CHASIN'--        


220
00:19:07,213 --> 00:19:09,780
        <i> CHRISTINE?</i>             
        <i> SOMEBODY TOOK MY SPOT.</i> 


221
00:19:09,849 --> 00:19:14,752
<i>AXE!</i>                            
YOUR HUSBAND'S GONE TWO WEEKS,  
AND ALL YOU CAN SAY IS "AXE"?   


222
00:19:14,820 --> 00:19:17,755
    - HOW'D IT GO?              
    -<i> AH, CAME UP EMPTY.</i>        


223
00:19:17,824 --> 00:19:20,124
                    WHO ARE YOU?


224
00:19:20,193 --> 00:19:22,226
        HI. I'M JAROD.          


225
00:19:22,294 --> 00:19:26,430
    - WHO'S THIS?               
    - UM, I CAN EXPLAIN. UH--   


226
00:19:26,499 --> 00:19:29,233
<i>WOULD YOU LOOK AT THEM EYES?</i>    
<i>DO YOU MIND?</i>                    


227
00:19:29,302 --> 00:19:31,802
<i>NO, NOT AT ALL.</i>                 


228
00:19:31,871 --> 00:19:34,038
        [ Chuckling ]           


229
00:19:34,107 --> 00:19:36,841
    THAT'S A FINE-LOOKING BOY.  
    IT-IT IS A BOY?             


230
00:19:36,910 --> 00:19:39,610
<i>YES.</i>                            
                    HEY, HEY.   


231
00:19:39,678 --> 00:19:41,913
                    <i> HEY, HEY.</i>  
    YOU LIKE KIDS?              


232
00:19:41,982 --> 00:19:43,914
                    LIKE 'EM?   


233
00:19:43,984 --> 00:19:48,152
    I'D HAVE A WHOLE TRIBE      
    IF CHRISTY WOULD COOPERATE. 


234
00:19:49,488 --> 00:19:52,590
    <i> YOU EVER NEED A BABYSITTER,</i>
    <i> I'M YOUR MAN.</i>              


235
00:19:52,659 --> 00:19:54,591
    I'LL REMEMBER THAT.         


236
00:19:54,660 --> 00:19:56,661
        BETTER MOVE THE TRUCK.  


237
00:19:59,699 --> 00:20:01,732
<i>[ Woman Over Scanner,</i>           
<i>  Indistinct ]</i>                  


238
00:20:02,968 --> 00:20:05,903
ANYTHING COME OVER THE SCANNER? 
<i>NOT YET.</i>                        


239
00:20:05,972 --> 00:20:08,673
WHY DID YOU LIE ABOUT AXE?      


240
00:20:10,510 --> 00:20:13,543
I GREW UP WITH                  
SEVEN BROTHERS AND SISTERS.     


241
00:20:13,612 --> 00:20:16,747
I WAS THE OLDEST,               
AND MY MOTHER WAS--             


242
00:20:16,816 --> 00:20:19,249
WELL, SHE WASN'T WHAT           
YOU'D CALL "HANDS ON."          


243
00:20:19,318 --> 00:20:21,451
        WHAT ABOUT YOUR FATHER? 


244
00:20:22,655 --> 00:20:25,656
HE WAS BUSY WITH                
HIS OTHER FAMILY ACROSS TOWN.   


245
00:20:25,725 --> 00:20:29,627
IT WAS UP TO ME TO MAKE SURE    
ARI AND WILLIAM WERE FED...     


246
00:20:29,696 --> 00:20:31,628
    AND MATTY WAS DRESSED,      


247
00:20:31,698 --> 00:20:35,900
AND JEREMY DIDN'T STAY UP LATE, 
 AND ELLA DID HER HOMEWORK.     


248
00:20:39,172 --> 00:20:42,473
I GOT OUT OF LITTLE ROCK        
AND MOVED IN WITH AXE.          


249
00:20:45,545 --> 00:20:49,647
I WANT TO BE ABLE TO THINK      
ABOUT CHRISTINE FOR A WHILE.    


250
00:20:49,715 --> 00:20:51,715
DOES THAT MAKE ME A BAD PERSON? 


251
00:20:51,784 --> 00:20:55,620
            NO.                 
            IT MAKES YOU HUMAN. 


252
00:20:58,291 --> 00:21:01,558
<i>[ Man ] SEE YOU LATER, FRANK.</i>   
<i>[ Woman Over Loudspeaker ]</i>      
<i>BILL, PICK UP LINE TWO.</i>         


253
00:21:05,298 --> 00:21:07,398
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>WE BETTER PUT IT UP</i>             
<i>ON THE LIFT.</i>                    


254
00:21:27,086 --> 00:21:29,420
<i>[ Woman Over Loudspeaker ]</i>      
<i>CHUCK, COME TO THE PARTS DESK.</i>  


255
00:21:52,678 --> 00:21:56,914
HEY, SPORT--                    
TAKE A LOOK AT THIS UNIT?       


256
00:21:59,619 --> 00:22:01,953
        NO PROBLEM.             


257
00:22:02,021 --> 00:22:05,522
<i>ACCIDENTALLY CLIPPED A JUNKIE</i>   
<i>WHO DECIDED NOT TO COOPERATE.</i>   


258
00:22:05,591 --> 00:22:08,558
<i>GUESS HE'LL COOPERATE NEXT TIME.</i>


259
00:22:10,597 --> 00:22:13,297
GET THIS UNIT FIXED.            
I WANNA GET OUT OF HERE FAST.   


260
00:22:13,365 --> 00:22:16,534
        <i> WHATEVER YOU SAY, UH,</i>  
        <i> DETECTIVE--</i>            


261
00:22:16,602 --> 00:22:18,568
        GEARY, DAVID W.         


262
00:22:20,206 --> 00:22:22,840
THOSE LOOK STRAIGHT TO YOU?     


263
00:22:25,545 --> 00:22:28,279
        - YEAH.                 
        - I'LL BE BACK.         


264
00:23:08,688 --> 00:23:10,688
    [ No Audible Dialogue ]     


265
00:23:31,110 --> 00:23:33,510
    <i> [ Broots ]</i>                 
    <i> OKAY, IT'S RIGHT</i>           
    <i> AROUND HERE SOMEWHERE.</i>     


266
00:23:33,580 --> 00:23:36,647
                    WHAT IS?    
        SEWER ACCESS.           


267
00:23:36,716 --> 00:23:39,784
BROOTS, THE SEWER MAIN IS ON    
THE OTHER SIDE OF THE COMPLEX.  


268
00:23:39,852 --> 00:23:42,987
        I KNOW.                 


269
00:23:43,056 --> 00:23:46,657
WHICH MAKES ME WONDER WHY       
THERE'S A MANHOLE COVER         
RIGHT HERE.                     


270
00:23:47,994 --> 00:23:49,961
HELP ME, SYDNEY.                


271
00:23:50,029 --> 00:23:52,229
        <i> [ Air Hissing ]</i>        
    OH!                         


272
00:23:52,297 --> 00:23:55,732
- [ Sydney ] CAN YOU SMELL THAT?
- SMELL IT? I CAN TASTE IT.     


273
00:23:57,136 --> 00:24:00,237
<i>[ Air Hissing ]</i>                 


274
00:24:04,310 --> 00:24:06,243
            AFTER YOU.          


275
00:24:08,914 --> 00:24:10,881
HOW-HOW DO YOU KNOW             
IT'S NOT WIRED DOWN THERE?      


276
00:24:10,950 --> 00:24:14,585
        <i> I RAN CENTRE SECURITY</i>  
        <i> FOR THREE YEARS.</i>       
        <i> I KNOW WHAT I'M DOING.</i> 


277
00:24:14,653 --> 00:24:16,988
YEAH, WELL, YOU DIDN'T KNOW     
ABOUT SL 27.                    


278
00:24:17,056 --> 00:24:18,722
            GET IN.             


279
00:24:21,059 --> 00:24:23,126
        YOU KNOW,               


280
00:24:23,195 --> 00:24:26,663
I'M NOT SURE                    
MY MEDICAL INSURANCE            
COVERS THIS SORT OF THING.      


281
00:24:27,767 --> 00:24:30,067
    SYDNEY, PUT SOME LIGHT      
    ON ME.                      


282
00:24:45,351 --> 00:24:47,952
            OW!                 


283
00:24:55,260 --> 00:24:57,260
        <i> [ Broots ]</i>             
        <i> WHAT DIED DOWN HERE?</i>   


284
00:24:57,330 --> 00:24:59,663
WHAT DIDN'T?                    


285
00:24:59,732 --> 00:25:01,666
    LET'S GO.                   


286
00:25:02,635 --> 00:25:04,635
OKAY.                           


287
00:25:08,107 --> 00:25:10,374
    [ Announcer, Indistinct ]   
<i>[ Axe Chuckles ]</i>                


288
00:25:10,443 --> 00:25:14,578
    YOU SEE THAT?               
    NOW SOMETIMES, IT'S BETTER  
    TO BE LUCKY THAN GOOD.      


289
00:25:14,647 --> 00:25:17,714
<i>ME AND MY OLD MAN</i>               
<i>USED TO WATCH HOOPS ON THE TUBE.</i>


290
00:25:17,783 --> 00:25:20,217
I FIGURED SOMEDAY,              
ME AND MY KID WOULD DO THE SAME.


291
00:25:21,987 --> 00:25:23,954
            CHRISTINE TOLD ME   
            WHAT'S GOING ON.    


292
00:25:24,023 --> 00:25:26,756
        <i> YOU REALLY THINK</i>       
        <i> THAT COP'S INVOLVED?</i>   


293
00:25:26,825 --> 00:25:31,828
<i>HIS NAME IS DAVID GEARY.</i>        
<i>HE'S A SPECIAL INVESTIGATOR</i>     
<i>FOR D.A. MITCH MEYERS.</i>          


294
00:25:31,897 --> 00:25:35,432
    - UGH, BUREAUCRATS.         
    - SOUNDS LIKE YOU'RE NOT    
      A BIG FAN OF CITY HALL.   


295
00:25:35,501 --> 00:25:38,235
        <i> I SPENT 20 YEARS</i>       
        <i> DRIVIN' A GARBAGE RIG</i>  
        <i> FOR THE CITY.</i>          


296
00:25:38,304 --> 00:25:41,505
    COUPLE OF MONTHS AGO,       
    I BLOW OUT MY BACK          
    LIFTIN' AN INDUSTRIAL BIN.  


297
00:25:41,574 --> 00:25:46,977
<i>CITY CANS ME,</i>                   
<i>CUTS OFF MY DISABILITY CHECKS.</i>  
<i>I CAN'T GET ANOTHER JOB.</i>        


298
00:25:47,046 --> 00:25:49,013
YOU'RE A GARBAGEMAN?            


299
00:25:49,081 --> 00:25:51,415
            SANITATION ENGINEER.


300
00:25:51,483 --> 00:25:53,750
    WOW.                        
            <i> YOU KNOW, JAROD,</i>   


301
00:25:53,819 --> 00:25:57,087
    I SEEN A LOT OF DIRTY THINGS
    ON THE STREET.              


302
00:25:57,156 --> 00:25:59,923
    BUT WHY ANYONE              
    WOULD WANT TO HURT SOMETHING
    AS WONDERFUL AS THIS...     


303
00:25:59,992 --> 00:26:02,426
            IS BEYOND ME.       


304
00:26:03,763 --> 00:26:06,363
                        <i> YEAH.</i>  


305
00:26:06,431 --> 00:26:09,667
        - [ Beeps ]             
        - WHAT'S THAT?          


306
00:26:11,637 --> 00:26:14,605
A MISSING PERSONS REPORT        
WAS JUST LOGGED ON TO           
THE POLICE DATABASE.            


307
00:26:14,673 --> 00:26:17,775
<i>IT'S THE FIRST MATCH</i>            
<i>I'VE FOUND.</i>                     


308
00:26:17,843 --> 00:26:21,012
JEANETTE CONNELLY.              
REPORTED MISSING BY             
HER NEXT-DOOR NEIGHBOR...       


309
00:26:21,080 --> 00:26:24,615
<i>ALONG WITH HER</i>                  
<i>FIVE-MONTH-OLD SON... MICHAEL.</i>  


310
00:26:29,788 --> 00:26:31,789
HELLO, MICHAEL.                 


311
00:26:33,392 --> 00:26:37,027
OF COURSE THERE'S               
A MISSING PERSONS ON HER.       
SHE'S MISSING.                  


312
00:26:37,095 --> 00:26:40,397
DON'T GET YOUR PANTIES          
IN A WAD.                       
EVERYTHING'S FINE.              


313
00:26:43,870 --> 00:26:47,137
<i>[ Woman Over Radio ]</i>            
<i>OFFICER'S REQUESTING BACKUP</i>     
<i>AT SAN PEDRO AND 9th.</i>           


314
00:27:24,010 --> 00:27:26,577
    [ Broots ]                  
    THERE MUST BE               
    A HUNDRED ROOMS DOWN HERE.  


315
00:27:28,581 --> 00:27:30,581
WHAT WAS THIS PLACE?            


316
00:27:33,819 --> 00:27:37,755
WHATEVER IT WAS,                
IT MUST'VE BEEN ONE HELL        
OF A FIRE THAT STOPPED IT.      


317
00:27:37,823 --> 00:27:42,459
YES. THERE WAS A RUMOR          
OF A FIRE IN THE SUMMER OF '82. 


318
00:27:42,528 --> 00:27:44,795
    I SPENT THAT SUMMER         
    IN FRANCE WITH MY FATHER.   


319
00:27:44,864 --> 00:27:47,097
I WISH I WAS THERE RIGHT NOW.   


320
00:27:47,166 --> 00:27:50,734
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>RUMOR IS IT WAS THE FIRE</i>        
<i>THAT LEFT RAINES...</i>             


321
00:27:50,803 --> 00:27:53,436
CHAINED TO HIS OXYGEN TANK.     


322
00:27:53,505 --> 00:27:55,405
            TOO BAD IT DIDN'T   
            FINISH THE JOB.     


323
00:27:55,474 --> 00:27:57,407
<i>[ Broots ]</i>                      
<i>HEY, LOOK.</i>                      


324
00:27:59,211 --> 00:28:03,647
            FOOTPRINTS.         
            AND THEY'RE FRESH.  


325
00:28:22,134 --> 00:28:24,134
                WHOA.           


326
00:28:35,815 --> 00:28:38,282
[ Broots ]                      
WHO PLAYED WITH TOYS DOWN HERE? 


327
00:28:42,054 --> 00:28:43,687
            <i> [ Miss Parker ]</i>    
            <i> A JACK-IN-THE-BOX?</i> 


328
00:28:51,397 --> 00:28:53,430
    <i> FASCINATING.</i>               


329
00:28:55,767 --> 00:28:58,302
            - BROOTS.           
            - HUH?              


330
00:28:58,371 --> 00:29:01,805
-<i> CHECK OUT THE SUIT.</i>           
-<i> [ Broots ] IT'S ALWAYS BROOTS.</i>


331
00:29:05,845 --> 00:29:09,813
        [ Yelling ]             
        THERE'S A-- THERE'S A   
        BULLET HOLE IN HIS EYE. 


332
00:29:12,284 --> 00:29:16,120
    - COME ON.                  
    - SOMEHOW, I GET THE FEELING
      HE'S THE LUCKY ONE.       


333
00:29:18,123 --> 00:29:19,656
<i>[ Beeping ]</i>                     


334
00:29:19,724 --> 00:29:22,659
<i>[ Raines ]</i>                      
<i>WHAT IS IT, ANGELO?</i>             


335
00:29:22,728 --> 00:29:25,095
<i>SUBLEVEL SECURITY ALERT?</i>        


336
00:29:25,163 --> 00:29:27,364
<i>[ Beeping Continues ]</i>           


337
00:29:32,170 --> 00:29:34,805
<i>[ Beeping Continues ]</i>           


338
00:29:34,874 --> 00:29:37,241
<i>[ Woman Over Police Radio,</i>      
<i>  Indistinct ]</i>                  


339
00:29:37,309 --> 00:29:39,376
            [ Jiggling Lock ]   


340
00:29:39,444 --> 00:29:41,678
            <i> SHE'S NOT THERE.</i>   


341
00:29:42,948 --> 00:29:45,649
POLICE OFFICER, MA'AM.          


342
00:29:45,718 --> 00:29:48,819
        IT'S NOT LIKE JEANETTE  
        TO DISAPPEAR,           
        NOT WITH THAT NEW BABY. 


343
00:29:48,888 --> 00:29:51,422
    <i> SHE'S A NICE GIRL, SMART.</i>  


344
00:29:51,490 --> 00:29:54,257
        I TOLD EVERYTHING       
        TO THE OTHER POLICEMAN. 
<i>OTHER POLICEMAN?</i>                


345
00:29:54,326 --> 00:29:57,561
    - WHEN?                     
    - TEN, 15 MINUTES AGO,      
      BEFORE YOU GOT HERE.      


346
00:29:57,629 --> 00:30:00,397
<i>- [ Man ] DISPATCH, THIS IS 36.</i> 
<i>- [ Man #2 ] GO, 36.</i>            


347
00:30:00,466 --> 00:30:03,400
    <i> [ Man #1 ]</i>                 
    <i> UH, WE FOUND A JUMPER BELOW</i>
    <i> THE EAST RIVER BRIDGE.</i>     


348
00:30:03,469 --> 00:30:05,936
<i>FEMALE CAUCASIAN, EARLY 20s,</i>    
<i>NO I.D.</i>                         


349
00:30:06,005 --> 00:30:11,542
MAY HAVE BEEN THERE A FEW DAYS. 
TRANSPORTING HER TO ST. MARY'S  
UNDER SUICIDE WATCH. OVER.      


350
00:30:11,610 --> 00:30:13,711
<i>[ Man #2 ]</i>                      
<i>COPY THAT, 36.</i>                  


351
00:30:13,779 --> 00:30:17,514
        WHAT ABOUT JEANETTE?    
DON'T WORRY, MA'AM.             
I'LL TAKE CARE OF JEANETTE.     


352
00:30:25,591 --> 00:30:27,957
            [ Broots ]          
            WHOA!               


353
00:30:33,198 --> 00:30:35,365
            <i> [ Glass Breaking ]</i> 
                        OH, GOD.


354
00:30:37,002 --> 00:30:40,070
                    <i> SYRINGES?</i>  


355
00:30:40,139 --> 00:30:41,705
            WHAT IS IT?         


356
00:30:43,175 --> 00:30:47,444
    <i> THIS PLACE HAS</i>             
    <i> ALL THE COMPONENTS</i>         
    <i> OF A SIM LAB.</i>              


357
00:30:47,513 --> 00:30:52,215
<i>[ Broots ]</i>                      
<i>I NEVER KNEW THERE WAS</i>          
<i>ANOTHER SIM LAB IN THE CENTRE.</i>  


358
00:30:52,284 --> 00:30:54,451
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>NEITHER DID I.</i>                  


359
00:31:04,864 --> 00:31:06,630
        <i> [ Broots ]</i>             
        <i> WHAT THE HELL IS THAT?</i> 


360
00:31:06,699 --> 00:31:08,631
    BIRTHING TABLE.             


361
00:31:09,868 --> 00:31:12,769
            WITH SHACKLES?      
            <i> [ Pager Beeping ]</i>  


362
00:31:12,838 --> 00:31:14,838
                    UH-OH.      


363
00:31:17,509 --> 00:31:20,810
    - IT'S MR. RAINES.          
    - WHAT ARE YOU WAITING FOR? 


364
00:31:43,268 --> 00:31:46,269
<i>MISS PARKER.</i>                    
WHAT IS THIS PLACE?             


365
00:31:48,040 --> 00:31:52,809
WHATEVER IT WAS,                
IT WASN'T A FILING ROOM.        


366
00:31:52,878 --> 00:31:56,346
    <i> THESE HAVEN'T BEEN BURNT.</i>  
    <i>  THESE WERE BROUGHT HERE.</i>  


367
00:31:56,415 --> 00:32:00,150
    ALL THESE FILES PERTAIN     
    TO THE PRETENDER PROJECT.   


368
00:32:05,524 --> 00:32:08,025
THIS BOX IS ALL ABOUT JAROD.    


369
00:32:16,468 --> 00:32:18,335
                WHAT IS THAT?   


370
00:32:20,906 --> 00:32:24,340
        A HOOD.                 
        MUST'VE BEEN JAROD'S.   


371
00:32:29,481 --> 00:32:32,983
SYDNEY, THERE IS                
NO DATE OF DEATH...             


372
00:32:33,052 --> 00:32:35,052
                LISTED FOR      
                JAROD'S PARENTS.


373
00:32:38,257 --> 00:32:42,225
AS FAR AS THESE DOCUMENTS       
ARE CONCERNED, THEY WERE ALIVE  
WHEN JAROD WAS BROUGHT HERE.    


374
00:32:43,929 --> 00:32:46,262
        JAROD WAS STOLEN.       


375
00:32:46,331 --> 00:32:50,467
I THINK YOU SHOULD              
LOOK AT THIS ENTRANCE RECORD.   


376
00:32:50,536 --> 00:32:55,071
THERE'S NO NAMES,               
NOTHING TO FOLLOW.              
                HMM.            


377
00:32:55,140 --> 00:32:58,675
    BUT THERE IS A SIGNATURE BY 
    A SPECIAL EXPEDITER WHO     
    BROUGHT JAROD TO THE CENTRE.


378
00:32:58,743 --> 00:33:02,378
        SPECIAL EXPEDITER--     
        JACOB.                  


379
00:33:05,517 --> 00:33:08,352
    THAT SIGNATURE              
    IS MY BROTHER-- JACOB.      


380
00:33:08,420 --> 00:33:10,921
<i>[ Cell Phone Ringing ]</i>          


381
00:33:13,158 --> 00:33:15,258
                    WHAT?       


382
00:33:15,327 --> 00:33:18,094
RAINES HAS ANGELO SANITIZING    
THE SECURITY SYSTEM.            


383
00:33:18,163 --> 00:33:21,064
DOES HE KNOW WHERE WE ARE?      
NO, I DON'T THINK SO.           


384
00:33:21,133 --> 00:33:23,733
    - YOU DON'T THINK?          
    - YES. NO! I DON'T KNOW!    


385
00:33:23,802 --> 00:33:27,470
IT WAS WEIRD.                   
RAINES WAS REAL SUSPICIOUS,     
AND ANGELO JUST KEPT GIGGLING.  


386
00:33:27,539 --> 00:33:29,472
AND, MAN, YOU'RE NOT GONNA      
BELIEVE HIS HEAD.               


387
00:33:29,541 --> 00:33:32,376
JUST KEEP YOURS COOL.           


388
00:33:32,444 --> 00:33:35,445
<i>IT'S RAINES.</i>                    
            HE KNOWS.           


389
00:33:35,513 --> 00:33:38,148
JUST GRAB THE FILES.            


390
00:33:38,216 --> 00:33:40,150
        THESE FILES HAVE BEEN   
        COLLECTED BY SOMEONE.   


391
00:33:40,218 --> 00:33:43,887
        REMOVING THEM           
        WILL AROUSE SUSPICION.  
THIS MAY BE OUR ONLY CHANCE.    


392
00:33:43,955 --> 00:33:46,990
    I WANT TO FIND OUT THE TRUTH
    AS MUCH AS YOU DO.          


393
00:33:47,058 --> 00:33:51,094
        <i> BUT AT THIS POINT,</i>     
        <i> CAUTION IS KEY.</i>        


394
00:34:26,765 --> 00:34:30,133
DETECTIVE DAVE GEARY.           
YOU'VE GOT THAT JANE DOE.       


395
00:34:31,603 --> 00:34:33,837
    <i> [ Jarod ] COME ON. COME ON.</i>


396
00:34:33,906 --> 00:34:35,672
<i>[ Woman ]</i>                       
<i>STILL CHECKING, DETECTIVE.</i>      


397
00:34:35,741 --> 00:34:38,007
SUICIDE ATTEMPT.                


398
00:34:38,076 --> 00:34:40,510
<i>[ Woman ]</i>                       
<i>IT'S JUST NOT COMING UP.</i>        


399
00:34:47,852 --> 00:34:49,485
                OH, HERE IT IS. 
                ROOM 708.       


400
00:35:02,201 --> 00:35:04,300
            JEANETTE.           
             JEANETTE, WAKE UP. 


401
00:35:07,305 --> 00:35:10,873
PLEASE, NO MORE.                
I DON'T NEED ANY MORE SEDATIVES.


402
00:35:10,942 --> 00:35:13,176
<i>I'M NOT CRAZY.</i>                  
            I KNOW.             


403
00:35:13,245 --> 00:35:15,178
OH, NO, NO.                     
I DIDN'T TRY TO KILL MYSELF.    


404
00:35:15,247 --> 00:35:17,814
THERE WAS A MAN,                
AND HE THREW ME OFF THE BRIDGE. 
IT WAS A POLICEMAN.             


405
00:35:17,883 --> 00:35:20,917
    WHY WON'T ANYONE BELIEVE ME?


406
00:35:20,986 --> 00:35:23,486
    - I BELIEVE YOU.            
    - WELL, WHO ARE YOU?        


407
00:35:25,123 --> 00:35:27,524
    MY NAME IS JAROD.           
    I'M HERE TO HELP YOU.       


408
00:35:30,562 --> 00:35:34,331
        - HE TOOK MY BABY.      
        - I HAVE YOUR BABY.     


409
00:35:34,399 --> 00:35:36,833
HE'S WITH ME.                   
                WHERE'S MICHAEL?


410
00:35:36,902 --> 00:35:39,636
HE IS SAFE, BUT WE MUST         
GET OUT OF THIS HOSPITAL.       


411
00:35:39,705 --> 00:35:41,905
THE MAN WHO TRIED TO KILL YOU   
IS HERE.                        


412
00:35:53,418 --> 00:35:57,754
<i>[ Woman Over P.A. ]</i>             
<i>DR. PETERSON, CALL YOUR SERVICE.</i>
<i>DR. PETERSON, CALL YOUR SERVICE.</i>


413
00:36:02,961 --> 00:36:05,027
        [ Chatter, Indistinct ] 


414
00:37:37,088 --> 00:37:39,022
<i>[ Engine Starting ]</i>             
<i>[ Tires Screeching ]</i>            


415
00:37:53,338 --> 00:37:56,072
I WAS SO AFRAID                 
 I WOULD NEVER SEE HIM AGAIN.   


416
00:38:00,211 --> 00:38:02,578
WHERE'D YOU FIND HIM?           


417
00:38:02,647 --> 00:38:05,481
        THAT'S NOT IMPORTANT.   


418
00:38:05,550 --> 00:38:08,184
            WHAT'S IMPORTANT IS 
            YOU'RE TOGETHER NOW.


419
00:38:09,254 --> 00:38:11,154
                    <i> JEANETTE,</i>  


420
00:38:11,223 --> 00:38:13,856
    WHY WOULD A POLICE DETECTIVE
    WANT YOU AND MICHAEL DEAD?  


421
00:38:16,694 --> 00:38:21,331
            <i> WAS IT BECAUSE OF</i>  
            <i> MITCH MEYERS?</i>      
YEAH.                           


422
00:38:21,400 --> 00:38:24,734
        IS MICHAEL MITCH'S SON? 


423
00:38:33,612 --> 00:38:37,180
I WAS WORKING AS AN INTERN      
IN HIS OFFICE.                  


424
00:38:37,249 --> 00:38:42,218
    I THOUGHT HE WAS GOOD.      
    I THOUGHT HE MEANT          
    THE THINGS THAT HE SAID.    


425
00:38:42,287 --> 00:38:44,720
    WE HAD AN AFFAIR.           


426
00:38:46,591 --> 00:38:49,893
    HE SAID HE DIDN'T LOVE      
    HIS WIFE ANYMORE,           
    AND HE WAS GONNA LEAVE HER. 


427
00:38:49,961 --> 00:38:52,228
I MEAN, I COULD BARELY          
PAY FOR MY RENT,                


428
00:38:52,297 --> 00:38:56,032
SO I TOLD HIM HE HAD TO TAKE    
RESPONSIBILITY FOR HIS SON.     


429
00:38:58,169 --> 00:39:00,103
                AND?            


430
00:39:00,171 --> 00:39:02,572
        HE SAID HE WOULD DO     
        THE RIGHT THING,        
        AND I-I BELIEVED HIM.   


431
00:39:02,641 --> 00:39:04,707
        I MEAN, I DIDN'T THINK--


432
00:39:07,846 --> 00:39:10,479
                IT'S OKAY.      


433
00:39:10,548 --> 00:39:14,650
    DETECTIVE GEARY CAME,       
    AND HE TOLD ME...           


434
00:39:14,719 --> 00:39:18,421
<i>THAT MITCH WANTED TO SEE ME</i>     
<i>BECAUSE HE WANTED TO HELP US.</i>   


435
00:39:18,489 --> 00:39:20,389
    AND I-- I DIDN'T THINK.     


436
00:39:20,458 --> 00:39:24,794
    WE JUST GOT IN THE CAR,     
    AND THE NEXT THING I KNEW,  


437
00:39:24,863 --> 00:39:29,332
I'M BEING DRAGGED OUT           
ON THE BRIDGE, AND ALL I COULD  
HEAR WAS MY MICHAEL CRYING.     


438
00:39:29,401 --> 00:39:32,568
            I OUGHTA BREAK      
            THE BASTARD'S NECK. 


439
00:39:32,637 --> 00:39:36,406
NOW CAN WE GO TO THE POLICE?    
                    <i> [ Jarod ]</i>  
                    <i> NO.</i>        


440
00:39:36,474 --> 00:39:39,509
            WE HAVE TO PLAY     
            A LITTLE POLITICS   
            WITH THE D.A. FIRST.


441
00:39:39,577 --> 00:39:42,646
        I WANNA HELP.           
        FOR MICHAEL.            


442
00:39:44,682 --> 00:39:47,083
    ISN'T TOMORROW GARBAGE DAY? 


443
00:39:55,727 --> 00:39:58,528
    MITCH MEYERS, PLEASE.       
    IT'S URGENT.                


444
00:40:02,734 --> 00:40:04,934
    [ Meyers ]                  
    JEANETTE, LISTEN TO ME.     


445
00:40:05,002 --> 00:40:07,002
            <i> WHEN HE WAS BORN--</i> 
        <i> [ Jeanette ]</i>           
        <i> HIS NAME IS MICHAEL.</i>   


446
00:40:07,071 --> 00:40:11,507
<i>RIGHT. WHEN MICHAEL WAS BORN,</i>   
<i>I THOUGHT I COULD FINALLY</i>       
<i>MAKE THE BREAK.</i>                 


447
00:40:11,576 --> 00:40:16,079
<i>THEN I STARTED THINKING HOW</i>     
<i>IT MIGHT LOOK-- MY WIFE, MY</i>     
<i>CHILDREN, YOU BEING SO YOUNG.</i>   


448
00:40:16,147 --> 00:40:20,116
EVERYTHING I HAVE WORKED FOR--  
ALL THE GOOD I HAVE DONE-- IT   
WOULD BE GOING DOWN THE DRAIN.  


449
00:40:20,185 --> 00:40:24,320
<i>SO YOU TRIED TO KILL US?</i>        
<i>NO, THAT'S NOT WHAT I WANTED.</i>   
<i>THAT'S NOT WHO I AM.</i>            


450
00:40:24,389 --> 00:40:26,322
                    <i> I LOVE YOU.</i>


451
00:40:26,391 --> 00:40:28,892
LOOK, IF YOU DON'T WANT         
THE TRUTH PLAYED OUT            
ON THE 11:00 NEWS,              


452
00:40:28,960 --> 00:40:34,530
YOU HAVE DETECTIVE GEARY        
BRING $50,000 TO THE ALLEY      
WHERE HE LEFT MICHAEL AT 2:00.  


453
00:40:57,321 --> 00:41:00,689
<i>[ Truck Approaching ]</i>           


454
00:41:14,806 --> 00:41:17,073
    POLICE OFFICER.             
    YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO TAKE   
    THIS TRASH ANOTHER TIME.    


455
00:41:17,141 --> 00:41:19,542
            <i> WE COLLECT IT NOW.</i> 


456
00:41:21,413 --> 00:41:24,280
YOU GUYS DON'T KNOW             
WHAT YOU'RE DOIN'.              


457
00:41:27,018 --> 00:41:29,519
            YOU FEELING NAKED?  


458
00:41:31,489 --> 00:41:35,525
    A LITTLE VULNERABLE?        
    IT'S TERRIFYING, ISN'T IT?  


459
00:41:35,593 --> 00:41:37,726
        BEING AT                
        SOMEONE ELSE'S MERCY,   


460
00:41:37,795 --> 00:41:40,729
    <i> COMPLETELY DEFENSELESS...</i>  


461
00:41:40,798 --> 00:41:43,632
        LIKE A LITTLE BABY...   


462
00:41:43,701 --> 00:41:46,235
    TOSSED IN A DUMPSTER        
    IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT. 


463
00:41:46,304 --> 00:41:49,305
            YOU THREW AWAY      
            AN INNOCENT BABY.   


464
00:41:49,373 --> 00:41:53,076
        <i> [ Click ]</i>              
I'VE BEEN WAITING FOR THIS      
MOMENT EVER SINCE I SAW YOU,    


465
00:41:53,145 --> 00:41:56,045
        STANDING IN THE ALLEY.  


466
00:41:57,515 --> 00:42:01,317
        AS DISTRICT ATTORNEY,   
        I HAVE WORKED HARD      
        FOR THIS CITY...        


467
00:42:01,386 --> 00:42:04,987
<i>TO REPAIR THE FAITH,</i>            
<i>THE BELIEF AND THE LEADERSHIP...</i>


468
00:42:05,056 --> 00:42:07,223
<i>OF YOUR ELECTED OFFICIALS.</i>      


469
00:42:07,292 --> 00:42:10,126
EXCUSE ME. MRS. MEYERS?         
HI.                             


470
00:42:10,195 --> 00:42:13,763
<i>MY NAME IS JEANETTE CONNELLY.</i>   
    ...FAMILY VALUES,           
    RESPONSIBILITIES--          


471
00:42:13,832 --> 00:42:16,799
YOUR HUSBAND AND I              
HAVE BEEN HAVING AN AFFAIR.     


472
00:42:16,868 --> 00:42:19,502
    I AM A MAN WHO              
    BELIEVES IN COMMITMENT.     


473
00:42:19,570 --> 00:42:22,505
    <i> JAN-- MY WIFE OF 15 YEARS--</i>


474
00:42:22,574 --> 00:42:24,640
    MY TWO BEAUTIFUL DAUGHTERS--
    JESSICA AND LINDSAY.        


475
00:42:24,709 --> 00:42:28,777
<i>I KNOW WHAT IT TAKES</i>            
<i>TO BUILD A SUCCESSFUL FAMILY.</i>   


476
00:42:28,846 --> 00:42:31,247
            <i> IT TAKES HONESTY.</i>  


477
00:42:31,316 --> 00:42:33,316
<i>[ Jeanette Over Speaker ]</i>       
<i>YOU TRIED TO KILL</i>               
<i>ME AND OUR SON.</i>                 


478
00:42:33,384 --> 00:42:35,852
    <i> [ Meyers Over Speaker ]</i>    
    <i> JEANETTE, LISTEN TO ME.</i>    


479
00:42:35,920 --> 00:42:40,356
I WAS FRIGHTENED OF             
WHAT YOU MIGHT DO, MIGHT SAY.   


480
00:42:40,425 --> 00:42:43,659
EVERYTHING I HAVE WORKED FOR--  
ALL THE GOOD I HAVE DONE-- IT   
WOULD BE GOING DOWN THE DRAIN.  


481
00:42:43,728 --> 00:42:47,497
    <i> SO YOU TRIED TO KILL US?</i>   
<i>NO, THAT'S NOT WHAT I WANTED.</i>   
<i>THAT'S NOT WHO I AM.</i>            


482
00:42:47,566 --> 00:42:49,632
I TOLD GEARY TO FRIGHTEN YOU.   
THAT'S ALL.                     


483
00:42:49,701 --> 00:42:54,303
    <i> I DIDN'T KNOW HE WAS GONNA</i> 
    <i> TAKE IT AS FAR AS MURDER.</i>  
    <i> YOU HAVE TO BELIEVE ME.</i>    


484
00:43:26,304 --> 00:43:28,538
        [ Groans ]              


485
00:43:29,540 --> 00:43:34,243
            OH! I ALMOST FORGOT.


486
00:43:35,313 --> 00:43:37,447
        <i> NOW THEY'RE STRAIGHT.</i>  


487
00:43:49,760 --> 00:43:52,128
            <i> [ Michael Crying ]</i> 


488
00:43:52,196 --> 00:43:54,297
                    THANKS, AXE.
        BYE-BYE TO JAROD.       


489
00:43:54,366 --> 00:43:56,966
                HEY. COME HERE. 
BYE, JAROD.                     


490
00:43:57,034 --> 00:43:59,101
            THANKS, CHRISTINE.  


491
00:43:59,170 --> 00:44:02,872
HEY, LITTLE MAN,                
IT WAS VERY NICE TO MEET YOU.   


492
00:44:02,940 --> 00:44:05,475
    I WANT YOU TO DO ME A FAVOR.


493
00:44:05,543 --> 00:44:08,711
            I WANT YOU TO ALWAYS
            LISTEN TO YOUR MOM. 


494
00:44:08,780 --> 00:44:12,715
        NEVER, EVER FORGET HER. 
        OKAY?                   


495
00:44:16,154 --> 00:44:18,188
THERE'S MY BOY.                 


496
00:44:18,256 --> 00:44:20,523
        HI! HOW'RE YOU DOIN'?   


497
00:44:22,994 --> 00:44:24,928
THANK YOU.                      
                GOOD LUCK.      


498
00:44:24,996 --> 00:44:27,530
THANK YOU.                      


499
00:44:27,599 --> 00:44:29,532
SAY BYE-BYE, SWEETIE.           
                            BYE.


500
00:44:29,601 --> 00:44:31,601
        BYE.                    


501
00:44:37,942 --> 00:44:40,409
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>BROOTS HAS CIRCUMVENTED</i>         
<i>THE SECURITY SENSORS.</i>           


502
00:44:40,478 --> 00:44:42,278
<i>WE HAVE 10 MINUTES.</i>             


503
00:44:42,347 --> 00:44:46,916
<i>LET'S JUST TAKE A CLOSER LOOK</i>   
<i>AT THOSE FILES</i>                  
<i>AND GET THE HELL OUT OF HERE.</i>   


504
00:44:51,456 --> 00:44:53,823
    IT'S ALL GONE.              


505
00:44:54,559 --> 00:44:56,592
                        RAINES. 


506
00:44:56,661 --> 00:44:59,328
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>NO. IF RAINES KNEW</i>              
<i>WE FOUND THOSE FILES,</i>           


507
00:44:59,397 --> 00:45:01,330
WE'D BE DEAD.                   


508
00:45:02,500 --> 00:45:05,534
            WELL, IF HE DIDN'T  
            TAKE THEM, WHO DID? 


509
00:46:42,033 --> 00:46:43,032
            [ Mews ]            


